<br>
<br>
<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> The Strategy is ...well.. fun.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Bid 7 and make him start. WOW! Your opponents eyes should now be at the size of water melons. (note: I bid 9 when I play a friendly game, just for fun. Haw haw haw)<br>
You do not need your site one, as it comes up with farmer anyway. This way you should get out the buckleberry ferry. And then earn a free site. And if your opponent do not have the map. You should also be able to hit him with all of your moria sites. The bedroom is also much nicer than the ford for you as a hobbit player.<br>
<br><br>
Hobbits move only once each turn. You can of course double move, but do this with extra! caution. And always remember to then use the map. do not run to his site 9? plz.. my hobbits do not like to overwhelmed by uruks.. And they certanly do not like to discard all of their allies at site seven. If you have map out, you CAN run for it. Just plz do not **** up and give yourself your own site 8 agains any orc deck... there is a chance he does not play with it.. Ok you can do that agains archers.. (brownlands suck, it is good that I own the rare ring.)<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Hobbit farmer and greenhill makes all of your allies free to play. That is huge! There is no better way to play something, than to play it but not play its cost.<br>
<br><br>
You then have a stronger fellowship, and your opponent does not get the chance to have a stronger dark side of badies. Whopa!!<br>
<br><br>
Play stealths all the time, do not be cheap. And if you have cards in your hand when your turn is done. just discard like hell. You WILL draw a new stealth next turn, do not worry.<br>
And remember the turbo O Al! card. It will save you from nozdruls anyday. What abot double moving from site 7 to 9. Have a O AL! out and filibert. First you cancel the frodo skrimish with AL and then the fierce with fatty. That wont make nazguls happy, I tell you. HAW HAW HAW<br>
Fighting swarms? no problem. we have stealth and of course  frying pan. kills of lots and lots of gobbos. Pluss the next turn I discard his swarm with half his deck on it. That is one busy Dildo(Bilbo).<br>
<br>
Did I say that this is also a hobbit hospital? well it is. If you do not kill of my hairy caps in one blow, I will be just as healty the next turn, and the turn after that.<br>
<br><br>
It is important to allways have a bunch of badies on your hand at all times. Hammer him with a cavetroll at site 3 if you can. Punish him for double moving from one to three. An early troll often kills both arwen and lego if he havent a turbo lucky staring had. like drawing an aragorn and a versatility. But hey. If he double moved he shold be at your site three. The bedroom. Last time I checked, that was not a forest or a river. KaBOOM!<br>
<br><br>
So if you opponent wants to double move, he will die. That is if he did not draw: thrors map. aragorn, his bow. and a couple of other nasty cards. But hey... If he does. Then those cards are used up, and what will then protect him in the depths of moria?<br>
<br><br>
Your worst fear is gandalf, the hairy bastard!<br>
<br><br>
Watch out for sleep and really really big fellowships. You shold manage to kill of over half his fellow ship in moria, but not all. Not if he has 9 companions. but what the heck. That is five dead companions. How will he now protect himself from another troll and a new swarm.. Hehe a dead gandalf (backstabbers should finish him off early, if you can) can not cast sleep. And if he tries to shoot down your goblins with aragorn or lego. That is fine. Let him wound his own men. Just remember to sacrifice armories in an abundance when it is really needed. <br>
<br>
Ever seen a 300 pound truckdriver cry? <br>
tip: kill of his frodo by saying "hmf" to his bows and flashing with your aromries? It is priceless!<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
That is it for now. You should figure it out yourself in time..<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br>
<br><br>
Just remember to have fun with your little guys. Both the hairy ones and the green ones<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
NOTE 1:<br>
Yes I know the deck has a bunch of rare cards in it, sorry about that. But I said advanced didnt I?<br>
If you do not have those cards you could put in wallcrawlers instead of the trolls. And maybe a enquea or two to punish those big fellowship. That is just fine, as you then will have, at most sites, a lot of extra twillight. (That wont happen when you play the troll.)<br>
The armories and the swarms are a must. sorry.. <br>
you can manage with just two swarms. And maybe a fill with fear instead of some of the armoies.<br>
BUT YOU REALLY NEED THE BALROG! I am putting my foot down now. And I do not meen the common one. sorry newbies..<br>
<br>
NOTE 2:<br>
Frying Pan<br>
cost 0, bearer must be a hobbit. +1 str<br>
exert bearer to wound a orc he/she is "fighting".<br>
<br>
for now...<br>
